Harbhajan Singh Accuses Jet Airways Pilot Of Racist & Violent Behaviour, Pleads Modi For Help
	 	 	 	 CONTENT 
Harbhajan Singh Accuses Jet Airways Pilot Of Racist & Violent Behaviour, Pleads Modi For Help

Harbhajan Singh Accuses Jet Airways Pilot Of Racist & Violent Behaviour, Pleads Modi For Help

Hospitality went for a toss when a Jet Airways pilot allegedly hurled racist abuses and behaved violently with the passengers. According to Indian cricketer, Harbhajan Singh, the pilot abused a differently-abled man and physically assaulted a lady.

sports360

Singh, who was travelling in the flight at the time, narrated the incident in a series of tweets. He escalated the same to Narendra Modi and expressed his disgust at the pilot's shameful conduct.

So called this Bernd Hoesslin a pilot with @jetairways called my fellow indian(u bloody indian get out of my flight)while he is earning here — Harbhajan Turbanator (@harbhajan_singh) April 26, 2017

Not only was he racist but physically assaulted a lady and abused a physically challenged man..absolutely disgraceful &shame on @jetairways — Harbhajan Turbanator (@harbhajan_singh) April 26, 2017

Strict action must b taken &such things should not be allowed or tolerated in r country.. #proudtobeindian let's get together and sort this — Harbhajan Turbanator (@harbhajan_singh) April 26, 2017

The incident is reminiscent of the United Airlines incident where a doctor was dragged off the aircraft in a brutal manner.

ndtv

In a statement, however, Jet Airways said that they will look into the matter and conduct a probe.

Regret the incident, initiated a full-fledged investigations, based on specific inputs from guests, concerned dept &agencies: Jet Airways — ANI (@ANI_news) April 26, 2017

What is up the airlines these days?

